The simplest way is instantiating as many [Thread][1] objects as you need like:

    for (int i = 0; i &lt; how_many_threads_do_you_want; i++) {
        Thread thread = new Thread() {
            public void run() {
                //your code to run JMeter here
            }
        }
        thread.start();
    }

For more complex scenarios like waiting for completion, inter-process communication, etc. see i.e. [ExecutorService][2]

Maybe instead of trying to re-invent the wheel you might want to use ready solutions like [Taurus automation framework][3]? 


